comments: Johnson (SAS) takes fewer than three steps after he has gathered the ball.
Aldridge (SAS) could be deemed to be imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Johnson (SAS) has a collapsed arm against his own body when contact with Tate (HOU) occurs during his driving shot attempt.  Johnson goes to, but not through Tate's space as he changes directions.
Johnson (SAS) briefly places his hand across Wood's (HOU) back as the two players engage in incidental leg contact during the pick. Johnson immediately removes his hand and the contact is marginal.
Tate (HOU) places two hands on the ball during Johnson's (SAS) drive. A jump ball is correctly assessed.
Tucker (HOU) maintains a legal guarding position during DeRozan's (SAS) driving shot attempt.
Johnson (SAS) steps into Wood's (HOU) path and he initiates foot to foot contact with Wood that affects his SQBR.
Correctly called kicked ball violation on Wood (HOU).
Tucker (HOU) legally contests DeRozan's (SAS) driving shot attempt.
Johnson (SAS) jumps vertically and he absorbs the oncoming body contact from Brown (HOU) during his driving shot attempt. Johnson avoids making contact to Brown's arm.

DeRozan (SAS) spins away from Tucker (HOU), who is in a legal guarding position with a forearm tucked against his body and he does not extend it.  The two players make incidental foot to foot contact.

Johnson (SAS) makes contact to Tucker's (HOU) arm that affects his FOM.  After communicating with the Replay Center, it is determined that the foul occurred with 0.4 seconds remaining on the game clock.
